It appears that the challenges in this area have already begun to manifest. Due to the FAA's stance on certain medications, I may have difficulty obtaining medical certification.
It's not impossible but will require a great deal of time and extra work.
Although this is a bit disappointing, it's just another problem that needs to be solved, and it does seem possible to solve it. It just requires a lot of time and money.
If you want to know what challenges I will face next:
The FAA doesn't like ADHD. If you're taking medication for ADHD, you're definitely not going to get your medical certificate.
